---
import Docs from "~/layouts/Docs.astro";
import { Code } from "astro:components";
import { DOCS_NAV } from "~/lib/docs-nav";
---

<Docs
  title="Ashlr Stack docs"
  description="The control plane for your entire dev stack — one command to provision, wire, and operate every third-party service in your project."
  eyebrow="Documentation"
>
  <h2>Three paths to Stack</h2>
  <p>
    Pick the one that matches where you are. You can mix and match — most users
    start with the quickstart, then come back for the CLI reference.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
    <a href="/docs/quickstart/" class="docs-card group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
        <span class="mono text-[11px] text-magenta-400 font-semibold">01</span>
        <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-ink-500">
          Install
        </div>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1.5 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        Quickstart
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        Install, <code class="mono text-ink-200">stack init</code>, then
        <code class="mono text-ink-200">stack add supabase</code>. Five minutes,
        real output.
      </p>
    </a>

    <a href="/docs/cli/" class="docs-card group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
        <span class="mono text-[11px] text-magenta-400 font-semibold">02</span>
        <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-ink-500">
          Add a service
        </div>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1.5 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        CLI reference
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        Every <code class="mono text-ink-200">stack</code> command with flags,
        defaults, and real examples.
      </p>
    </a>

    <a href="/docs/providers/" class="docs-card group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 mb-3">
        <span class="mono text-[11px] text-magenta-400 font-semibold">03</span>
        <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-ink-500">
          Browse
        </div>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-1.5 group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
        Providers
      </h3>
      <p class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 leading-relaxed">
        39 curated providers. What each one wires, which MCP it brings online,
        where its dashboard is.
      </p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>What Stack is</h2>
  <p>
    Stack is a thin control plane over the services your app actually uses. It
    drives the provider login, creates upstream resources (a Supabase project,
    a Neon DB, a Sentry project), fetches their credentials, hands the secrets
    to <a href="/docs/phantom/">Phantom</a> for encryption, and wires
    <code>.env.local</code>, <code>.mcp.json</code>, and <code>.stack.toml</code>
    in one shot.
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`# before: 45 minutes across 6 tabs
# after:
stack add supabase`}
    lang="bash"
    theme="github-dark-dimmed"
  />

  <h2>What Stack isn't</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Not a secret manager.</strong> Every secret is stored by
      <a href="/docs/phantom/">Phantom</a>. Stack only knows the <em>slot
      names</em>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Not a deploy tool.</strong> We don't rebuild Vercel or Railway —
      we just give them the keys they need.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Not a lock-in.</strong> Everything writes to standard files:
      <code>.env</code>, <code>.mcp.json</code>, <code>.stack.toml</code>
      (TOML). Rip Stack out and your project still boots.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The whole map</h2>
  <p>Everything in these docs, grouped by purpose:</p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-6 space-y-6">
    {DOCS_NAV.map((group) => (
      <div>
        <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-ink-500 mb-3">
          {group.title}
        </div>
        <ul class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
          {group.items.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a
                href={item.href}
                class="block py-2 px-3 rounded-md hover:bg-white/[0.03] border border-transparent hover:border-white/[0.06] transition-colors group"
              >
                <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-3">
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-medium text-white group-hover:text-magenta-200 transition-colors">
                      {item.label}
                    </div>
                    {item.blurb && (
                      <div class="text-[13px] text-ink-400 mt-0.5" set:html={item.blurb.replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code class="mono text-ink-200">$1</code>')} />
                    )}
                  </div>
                  <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" class="text-ink-600 group-hover:text-magenta-400 transition-colors mt-1 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M3 3 L9 3 L9 9 M3 9 L9 3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>Pre-alpha status</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-warn">
    <strong>Heads up:</strong> Stack is <strong>v0.1</strong> — pre-alpha. Interfaces
    are still moving, some OAuth apps aren't yet registered (so a handful of
    providers fall back to paste-a-token flows), and error messages will get
    cleaner with each release. See the <a href="/docs/faq/">FAQ</a> for the
    honest caveats.
  </div>
</Docs>
